+### TeamPlayerSnapshot Lifecycle
+
+`TeamPlayerSnapshot` rows represent the locked squad composition for a team in a specific round. They are the source-of-truth for scoring: `calculateRoundPoints` sums `ScoringEvent.points` for players listed in a team's snapshot.
+
+**When snapshots are materialised:**
+
+| Event | Mechanism |
+|---|---|
+| Manager submits/updates squad (any time during `pre_round` or `active`) | `teams.saveSquad` writes/replaces snapshot rows for the current round |
+| Round is finalised (`gameweek.finaliseRound`) | `backfillRoundSnapshots` (called automatically before point calculation) writes snapshots derived from current `TeamPlayer` rows for any team that has no snapshot yet |
+
+**Guarantee:** By the time `calculateRoundPoints` runs for a round, every team with at least one `TeamPlayer` row will have a corresponding `TeamPlayerSnapshot` for that round. Teams that never submitted a squad (no `TeamPlayer` rows) will score 0 points.
+
+**Idempotency:** `backfillRoundSnapshots` uses `skipDuplicates: true` and skips teams that already have a snapshot — safe to call multiple times.
+
+See `packages/server/src/utils/scoring.ts` for the `backfillRoundSnapshots` implementation.
+
